-- PRESS DIGEST -China - Sept 17 
-- By Shanghai Newsroom
-- Tue Sep 16, 2014 09:52PM EDT
-- None



SHANGHAI, Sept 17 (Reuters) - Chinese newspapers available in Beijing and Shanghai carried the following stories on Wednesday. Reuters has not checked the stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

CHINA SECURITIES JOURNAL - Data from the Ministry of Housing and Urban-Rural Development shows China has reached investments worth 950 billion yuan in ($154.57 billion) affordable housing in the first eight months of the year.  SECURITIES TIMES - Traders in China opened a total of 170,690 new trading accounts last week, up 7.4 percent from a week earlier and hitting the highest level in nearly six months, data from China Securities Depository and Clearing Corporation Ltd showed.  CHINA BUSINESS NEWS - The Hubei province has released six policies to support its property industry, including a 30 percent discount on interest rates for first-home mortgages.  CHINA DAILY - Last year in China, there were 6,234 criminal cases where the plaintiff contested the judgment of the court, a significant rise from 2011, according to the Supreme People's Procuratorate. Of these 2,433 were reversed.